Preheat your oven to 220°C. Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Peel the @baking potato{1} and slice into thin rounds approximately 1cm thick.

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until just tender, ~{14-16%minutes}.
> TIP: The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through, but be careful not to overcook them.

Once cooked, carefully drain in a #colander{} and set aside.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced). Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}(thinly sliced). Trim the @carrot{3}(trimmed and halved lengthways), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots onto a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer, then set aside.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} and @olive oil{2%tbsp} into a #small bowl{}, then season. Mix together, then set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

When hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Cook until browned all over, ~{6-7%minutes}.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.
> TIP: Cook in batches if necessary - you want the chicken to brown, not stew.

Once browned, transfer the chicken to a #medium bowl{} and set aside.

Return your (now empty) pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{}. When hot, add the onion and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Add the mushrooms and a little more @olive oil{} if needed, then turn the heat up slightly and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Meanwhile, pop the carrots on the middle shelf of your oven to roast until tender, ~{18-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

If you've chosen to add bacon lardons to your meal, add @british smoked bacon lardons{90%g} to the pan first. Cook until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. Then add the onion and continue.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Stir the @water{100%ml} and the @chicken stock paste{10%g} into the pan, then bring to the boil.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, bring back to the boil again, then turn down the heat.

Simmer gently until reduced by a third, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the sauce has reduced, taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then return the chicken to the frying pan.

Transfer the chicken filling to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Layer on the cooked potato slices, then sprinkle over the breadcrumb mixture.

Season with @ground black pepper{} and bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{10-12%minutes}.
> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Serve straight from the dish with the roasted carrots alongside. Enjoy!